{
  "config_version": 36,
  "_comment": "Declarative policy for how the wizard applies the shipped build-config onto a device. Bump build.json config_version whenever ANY file under config/ changes. Modes: replace (overwrite whole file), seed_if_absent (write only if missing), merge_id (per <setting id>, build value wins - CLOBBERS user changes), merge_seed (per <setting id>, add-if-absent - our value is the DEFAULT but a user's own change is NEVER overwritten), merge_name (per <source><name>, add build's, keep user's). To DELIBERATELY push a changed default to every device with merge_seed: add that id to the file's optional \"force_ids\" list (overwrites even user-set values) and bump config_version; remove it once propagated if you want user changes to stick again. exclude_ids always win over force_ids to protect credentials. gears_settings enforces critical values in Gears' binary settings.db.",
  "files": [
